On January 10, 2021, President of the United States issued a proclamation to honor the service and sacrifice of United States Capitol Police Officers Brian D. Sicknick and Howard Liebengood, as well as all Capitol Police Officers and law enforcement across the country. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at the White House, public buildings and grounds, military posts, naval stations, naval vessels, and all federal government facilities in the District of Columbia and throughout the United States and its territories and possessions until sunset on January 13, 2021. The flag will also be flown at half-staff for the same period of time at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations. The proclamation was signed on January 10, 2021.